		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=492"><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>162 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.62]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Why, Pusbag?&nbsp;&nbsp;Why do we see people in the game who beg for items?  Why do we see people who have better items than we do beg for these things?  Why do we see level 40 monks/shaman/insert class here doing things that any person who has actually PLAYED the class knows are incredibly stupid?  Because people want the easy way out.  Why work for it when you can have someone else give it to you?  Why do 30 minutes of research when you are missing out on "phat lewtz"?  Why devote time to playing the game, when you can have your "Uber" 55 level druid friends plevel you d00d?  I don't have anything against people who have played this game since release wanting to get past level 25 quickly.  I mean, how many times can you kill rats and snakes and it not get old?  But when you get people who have no clue......<br><br>I guess you will ask why then do I continue to answer things.  It is because I sincerely believe that some of the topics NEED to be on the front page. And I also believe that some people are asking out of true newbieness.  Not because they are lazy, but because they do not know any different.  Does this make them bad?  No.  It does get old, but I know from helping my parents and relatives with their experiences with the internet what may seem blatently obvious to us, is dark and mysterious to others.<br><br>What makes a good puller?  Are weapons better than fists?  Why didn't feign death work for me?  Is there anywhere but XXX to train?  What is Kiting?  I do not mind answering these.  If you notice, I do not answer them everytime =)  <br><br>Don't worry.  It is not like you need another /ignore slot.  You can just happily skip these people, and rate our posts who do answer very generously since you don't feel you wish to do it yourself =)<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>Drindal<br>35 Monk BB (almost 36...)</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
